row, or record
column, or field,

To select multiple columns from a table, simply separate the column names with commas

* a shortcut to select all columns from a table (All details)
LIMIT to limit the number of rows returned

DISTINCT select all the unique values from a column,

COUNT count the number of rows in one or more columns.
	COUNT(*) tells you how many rows are in a table.
	COUNT() tells you how many rows are on just that column.
	COUNT(DISTINCT birthdate) to count the number of distinct values in a column.
	
Ex:
	SELECT COUNT(release_year)
	FROM films
	WHERE release_year < 2000;
